title: Corey Coleman breaks Baylor record, proceeds to do post-game presser shirtless
text:
Corey Coleman breaks Baylor record, proceeds to do post-game presser shirtless 
Corey Coleman has been the most productive wide receiver in college football this season. Getty Images Oct 24, 2015 at 5:57p ET 0Shares 
Baylor wide receiver Corey Coleman broke Kendall Wright's all-time school record for touchdown catches Saturday. He snagged two against Iowa State in a 45-27 victory, upping his total to 18 this year. That's more than any FBS receiver notched all of last season. 
Baylor WR Corey Coleman didn’t feel the need to put a shirt on at post-game presser https://t.co/ALIrKryKda pic.twitter.com/QUTED5czSL — Bleacher Report (@BleacherReport) October 24, 2015 
So, yeah, it's safe to say Coleman is having a historic season. And after Baylor's win today, the talented wideout decided to celebrate the record by... not wearing a shirt to his post-game press conference? Alright then. MORE NEWS: Want stories delivered to you? Sign up for our College Football newsletters. 

He's no Russell Westbrook at the podium, that's for sure. The Bears are now 7-0 on the year. 0
